1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,300
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,300 --> 00:00:02,600
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:04,500 --> 00:00:05,800
You don't need to apologize.

4
00:00:06,900 --> 00:00:07,900
I'm okay.

5
00:00:09,600 --> 00:00:10,600
Let's go inside.

6
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:12,600
Team Manager.

7
00:00:13,800 --> 00:00:17,000
I...

8
00:00:19,733 --> 00:00:20,733
like you.

9
00:00:27,033 --> 00:00:28,333
I...

10
00:00:31,333 --> 00:00:32,400
like you...

11
00:00:34,200 --> 00:00:35,200
very much.

12
00:00:38,133 --> 00:00:39,133
A whole lot.

13
00:00:49,500 --> 00:00:50,500
Ms. Cho Eun Ae,

14
00:00:51,600 --> 00:00:54,400
I'll pretend I didn't hear
what you just said.

15
00:00:55,333 --> 00:00:56,333
Why?

16
00:00:57,500 --> 00:00:58,600
Why should you?

17
00:01:00,133 --> 00:01:03,433
Because you'll be leaving in a few months?

18
00:01:05,300 --> 00:01:08,000
What does that have to do
with me liking you?

19
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:09,400
How could it not?

20
00:01:09,933 --> 00:01:11,533
Why walk down a road
with an obvious ending?

21
00:01:11,533 --> 00:01:13,200
No one knows how it'll end.

22
00:01:14,233 --> 00:01:18,000
It hasn't even happened yet.

23
00:01:18,133 --> 00:01:19,133
No.

24
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:22,533
My ending has already been decided, so...

25
00:01:22,533 --> 00:01:23,600
I tried to hold back.

26
00:01:25,733 --> 00:01:27,000
I even tried to stop.

27
00:01:28,800 --> 00:01:33,100
But I can't hold it in anymore.

28
00:01:35,233 --> 00:01:37,333
I just can't make it stop.

29
00:01:44,100 --> 00:01:45,100
What about you?

30
00:01:47,633 --> 00:01:48,633
Have you...

31
00:01:50,300 --> 00:01:52,000
never liked me?

32
00:01:54,500 --> 00:01:55,700
I think I know.

33
00:01:57,900 --> 00:01:58,900
I can feel it.

34
00:02:01,233 --> 00:02:02,233
You feel the same way about me too...

35
00:02:28,733 --> 00:02:29,733
You're right.

36
00:02:30,233 --> 00:02:32,900
I like you very much too, Ms. Cho Eun Ae.

37
00:02:33,833 --> 00:02:37,433
But once I leave this time,
I'm never coming back.

38
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:46,700
You have your beloved family...

39
00:02:47,700 --> 00:02:48,800
and the life you want here.

40
00:02:50,200 --> 00:02:53,533
I don't want to irresponsibly
shake up your life because of my feelings.

41
00:02:54,600 --> 00:02:55,600
So...

42
00:02:57,800 --> 00:02:59,633
Let's stop here.

43
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:02,000
Coward.

44
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:05,233
Right now,

45
00:03:06,800 --> 00:03:08,500
you're hiding behind...

46
00:03:08,500 --> 00:03:11,133
the word "responsibility," aren't you?

47
00:03:13,300 --> 00:03:16,100
You're right. I am a coward.

48
00:03:18,733 --> 00:03:19,900
This is my choice.

49
00:03:22,600 --> 00:03:26,433
I don't care what choice you make.

50
00:03:29,333 --> 00:03:32,700
Because I'm going to keep liking you.

51
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:38,800
Let's go inside.

52
00:03:39,400 --> 00:03:41,233
We need to prepare for the second round
starting tomorrow.

53
00:04:13,800 --> 00:04:16,033
Why are you standing there like a statue?

54
00:04:16,033 --> 00:04:17,033
Aren't you going to sleep?

55
00:04:17,433 --> 00:04:19,733
What? Right. I should.

56
00:04:32,500 --> 00:04:35,400
Eun Ae, I'm sorry, but could you...

57
00:04:35,400 --> 00:04:38,000
let me have the bed tonight
without playing rock-paper-scissors?

58
00:04:39,033 --> 00:04:41,800
I slept hunched over my desk
in the studio last night.

59
00:04:42,833 --> 00:04:44,100
Okay, fine.

60
00:04:48,900 --> 00:04:50,600
What's wrong? Did something happen?

61
00:04:53,533 --> 00:04:55,000
Did you and Team Manager...

62
00:04:55,300 --> 00:04:58,000
You should sleep. I'm going to wash up.

63
00:05:03,100 --> 00:05:04,700
How are things with Chief Ko these days?

64
00:05:05,200 --> 00:05:06,300
What do you mean?

65
00:05:06,533 --> 00:05:07,800
Is there really no chance at all?

66
00:05:09,500 --> 00:05:11,600
Min Ho is a good man.

67
00:05:12,333 --> 00:05:14,500
He's a little rough and simple,

68
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:17,200
but he's sincere and passionate.

69
00:05:19,033 --> 00:05:21,800
But just because he's a good person...

70
00:05:22,133 --> 00:05:24,400
doesn't mean he's the person I want.

71
00:05:26,200 --> 00:05:29,600
Will your feelings for Gyeol never change?

72
00:05:30,700 --> 00:05:32,200
Even if there's someone else
in Gyeol's life?

73
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:35,033
How do you know that?

74
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:37,000
Seung Ri.

75
00:05:38,733 --> 00:05:39,933
What did I tell you earlier?

76
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:44,533
Find a clear target first,
then charge straight ahead.

77
00:05:45,233 --> 00:05:48,033
Yes, and that's exactly
what I'm planning to do.

78
00:05:49,133 --> 00:05:51,100
Think again about what I said.

79
00:05:52,800 --> 00:05:56,233
Before charging ahead,
you need to find the target first.

80
00:05:57,433 --> 00:05:59,300
If you've chosen the wrong target,

81
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:01,733
you need to know when to lower your sword.

82
00:06:04,233 --> 00:06:06,600
If you keep pushing your blade
toward the wrong target...

83
00:06:06,900 --> 00:06:09,800
No, my target is clear.

84
00:06:10,700 --> 00:06:12,700
I just haven't charged straight ahead yet.

85
00:06:15,233 --> 00:06:16,233
Seung Ri.

86
00:06:26,200 --> 00:06:28,200
Eun Hyeong, did your lecture just end?

87
00:06:28,700 --> 00:06:29,700
Hey, Cho Rong.

88
00:06:30,200 --> 00:06:33,033
Do you have a minute to talk?

89
00:06:33,900 --> 00:06:36,000
Ji Seon went to Bit Na's kindergarten?

90
00:06:36,433 --> 00:06:39,800
Yeah.
She held Bit Na and cried for a long time.

91
00:06:41,500 --> 00:06:42,733
I had a feeling that day.

92
00:06:45,700 --> 00:06:48,300
When did Eun Hyeong get here?

93
00:06:48,600 --> 00:06:51,200
Just a little while ago, ma'am.

94
00:06:52,200 --> 00:06:54,933
I dragged him in
because I had something to tell him.

95
00:06:55,333 --> 00:06:58,100
He's spent all day teaching children,

96
00:06:58,500 --> 00:07:00,533
and he's probably almost dying of hunger.

97
00:07:00,533 --> 00:07:03,400
Why are you keeping him here
and chattering away?

98
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:05,133
I'm not chattering.

99
00:07:05,700 --> 00:07:07,933
If you're hungry,
should I make you some bindaetteok?

100
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:09,833
I've developed a new menu item.

101
00:07:10,233 --> 00:07:11,933
No, it's too late.

102
00:07:13,133 --> 00:07:15,400
I'd better head in. Good night.

103
00:07:15,900 --> 00:07:17,800
- Okay.
- Cho Rong, you sleep well too.

104
00:07:21,200 --> 00:07:23,533
Little bro, isn't your back uncomfortable?

105
00:07:24,200 --> 00:07:25,700
No, I'm fine.

106
00:07:30,400 --> 00:07:31,800
Excuse me, big bro.

107
00:07:33,333 --> 00:07:37,533
Have you ever truly loved someone?

108
00:07:39,900 --> 00:07:40,900
Of course.

109
00:07:42,200 --> 00:07:45,100
I truly love Ji Seon and Bit Na.

110
00:07:47,833 --> 00:07:50,000
Even though we're going through a divorce
right now,

111
00:07:52,700 --> 00:07:54,400
I loved Bit Na's mom very much.

112
00:07:55,833 --> 00:07:58,533
If you don't mind me asking,

113
00:07:59,633 --> 00:08:02,900
why did you separate?

114
00:08:05,133 --> 00:08:07,000
It may sound melodramatic,

115
00:08:09,500 --> 00:08:10,500
but it was because I loved her.

116
00:08:12,500 --> 00:08:16,233
The person I love
desperately wants to leave me.

117
00:08:18,800 --> 00:08:20,533
What else can I do?

118
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:23,333
Other than let her go.

119
00:08:26,033 --> 00:08:28,800
That's unfortunate.
I didn't expect that reason.

120
00:08:32,700 --> 00:08:35,200
Is there someone you like?

121
00:08:35,633 --> 00:08:36,633
Sorry?

122
00:08:38,933 --> 00:08:42,100
There is someone.

123
00:08:44,600 --> 00:08:45,600
That's nice.

124
00:08:46,800 --> 00:08:49,200
If it's someone you like,

125
00:08:50,100 --> 00:08:52,200
then I'm sure
she's a truly wonderful person.

126
00:08:53,333 --> 00:08:55,500
I hope you have
a happy and fulfilling love.

127
00:08:56,400 --> 00:08:59,700
I want that too,
but it doesn't seem possible.

128
00:09:01,400 --> 00:09:02,600
Why not?

129
00:09:05,433 --> 00:09:06,433
Because...

130
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:09,133
I'm a coward.

131
00:09:10,900 --> 00:09:12,900
I'm afraid of being in a situation
where I can't take responsibility,

132
00:09:14,633 --> 00:09:16,200
so I can't even bring myself to start.

133
00:09:17,533 --> 00:09:18,933
The ending is just too obvious.

134
00:09:20,233 --> 00:09:22,800
There is no such thing
as an obvious ending in this world.

135
00:09:24,133 --> 00:09:26,133
We create our own endings.

136
00:09:27,500 --> 00:09:28,700
Lu Xun once said,

137
00:09:29,400 --> 00:09:31,833
"There was no road in the world,"

138
00:09:32,600 --> 00:09:36,133
"but when people walked on it,
a road was made."

139
00:09:37,300 --> 00:09:41,800
I don't want her to get hurt
because of me.

140
00:09:43,500 --> 00:09:47,433
So I'm just going to drop it.

141
00:09:51,800 --> 00:09:52,800
Little bro,

142
00:09:54,100 --> 00:09:56,500
if love were something
that could be dropped...

143
00:09:56,500 --> 00:09:58,600
or stopped just because you wanted to,

144
00:09:59,333 --> 00:10:03,000
there would've been no Romeo and Juliet,
and no Chunhyang and Lee Mongryong.

145
00:10:04,433 --> 00:10:06,033
That precious feeling...

146
00:10:06,033 --> 00:10:08,400
may be the only one of its kind
in your life.

147
00:10:09,700 --> 00:10:11,400
So I hope you never let it slip away.

148
00:10:26,700 --> 00:10:28,500
Crystal, what's with the mask?

149
00:10:30,800 --> 00:10:32,900
No matter how much I practice,

150
00:10:32,900 --> 00:10:34,933
I just wasn't born with a poker face.

151
00:10:35,733 --> 00:10:37,633
I can't bear to look at Mother normally.

152
00:10:38,400 --> 00:10:40,500
But if you wear a mask,
how are you supposed to eat?

153
00:10:41,233 --> 00:10:42,300
That's true.

154
00:10:49,300 --> 00:10:50,633
What's this, Crystal?

155
00:10:51,100 --> 00:10:53,433
Are you going to wear that sun visor
at the dinner table with Father?

156
00:10:53,933 --> 00:10:55,000
Isn't that a bit much?

157
00:10:57,133 --> 00:10:58,600
Then what am I supposed to do?

158
00:10:59,433 --> 00:11:01,200
Yesterday I came in wearing sunglasses,

159
00:11:01,500 --> 00:11:03,333
and Father scolded me,

160
00:11:03,400 --> 00:11:05,300
asking why I was wearing
sunglasses indoors.

161
00:11:05,833 --> 00:11:07,000
Let's see...

162
00:11:07,800 --> 00:11:09,800
Why don't we just skip the meal?

163
00:11:09,800 --> 00:11:10,833
What?

164
00:11:10,833 --> 00:11:12,700
Rather than wearing that thing...

165
00:11:12,700 --> 00:11:14,533
and eating at the same table
with Father and Mother,

166
00:11:14,733 --> 00:11:17,633
just stay hungry, and Mother
will eventually go back to her room.

167
00:11:17,800 --> 00:11:19,600
Then you can come out and eat afterward.

168
00:11:19,600 --> 00:11:21,200
What?

169
00:11:21,200 --> 00:11:23,700
I skipped meals
because I was so shocked the other day,

170
00:11:23,700 --> 00:11:25,133
and now I'm starving.

171
00:11:26,633 --> 00:11:29,033
But is that password definitely right?

172
00:11:29,333 --> 00:11:30,633
Is it 0204?

173
00:11:30,800 --> 00:11:32,400
It has to be.

174
00:11:33,033 --> 00:11:36,033
If the photo you saw really was Mother,

175
00:11:36,300 --> 00:11:38,533
then that child
is definitely Kang Yeon Ja.

176
00:11:38,833 --> 00:11:42,100
And since the password is her birthday,
it has to be right.

177
00:11:42,100 --> 00:11:43,433
One hundred percent.

178
00:11:44,200 --> 00:11:47,600
But we'll need them to go out
before we can open the safe.

179
00:11:48,800 --> 00:11:51,800
Lately, they hardly go anywhere
except for walks in the garden.

180
00:11:52,200 --> 00:11:53,200
Exactly.

181
00:11:53,900 --> 00:11:56,700
It'd be perfect
if Gyeol took them somewhere...

182
00:11:56,700 --> 00:11:59,000
like on a trip again.

183
00:11:59,800 --> 00:12:03,700
Right. Should we suggest
they visit Gyeol's place?

184
00:12:04,533 --> 00:12:06,000
They're absolutely devoted to Gyeol.

185
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:08,100
If Gyeol invites them, they won't refuse.

186
00:12:08,600 --> 00:12:10,600
Crystal, you're driving me crazy.

187
00:12:10,600 --> 00:12:12,933
How is your brain working so well
these days?

188
00:12:13,100 --> 00:12:14,133
Exactly.

189
00:12:14,133 --> 00:12:16,700
Even I'm surprising myself lately.

190
00:12:16,700 --> 00:12:18,900
My little schemes
are working so brilliantly.

191
00:12:19,600 --> 00:12:20,833
Too brilliantly.

192
00:12:21,100 --> 00:12:22,900
All right. I'll go to work
and tell Gyeol...

193
00:12:23,200 --> 00:12:24,800
to invite his grandpa and grandma over.

194
00:12:24,800 --> 00:12:25,800
You promise.

195
00:12:26,833 --> 00:12:30,500
By the way, you know you have
one more thing to do, right?

196
00:12:31,600 --> 00:12:34,400
Make Mr. Cho handwrite
his resignation letter and leave.

197
00:12:35,200 --> 00:12:36,333
That's an excellent point.

198
00:12:36,333 --> 00:12:39,800
Make him get fed up
and quit the company on his own?

199
00:12:39,800 --> 00:12:41,000
Right.

200
00:12:41,733 --> 00:12:43,500
- Seriously.
- Seriously, he might actually quit.

201
00:12:50,800 --> 00:12:53,400
Mom, what's with that hat?

202
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:57,633
Don't you know ultraviolet rays
are the main cause of skin aging?

203
00:12:58,000 --> 00:13:00,033
Just because we're indoors
doesn't mean UV rays can't get in.

204
00:13:00,300 --> 00:13:03,900
It seems like
you're getting a few age spots.

205
00:13:03,900 --> 00:13:07,533
Just keep wearing it all the time,
even at home.

206
00:13:08,233 --> 00:13:11,400
Even so, wearing that at the dinner table?

207
00:13:11,633 --> 00:13:12,633
Take it off right now.

208
00:13:12,633 --> 00:13:15,800
No. This hat is the one thing
I absolutely can't take off.

209
00:13:16,100 --> 00:13:17,100
Mom.

210
00:13:19,500 --> 00:13:21,500
- Let's eat.
- Please enjoy.

211
00:13:24,400 --> 00:13:27,233
Why are you suddenly asking me to drive?

212
00:13:27,700 --> 00:13:29,933
I have to trim the garden...

213
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:32,433
and go grocery shopping with the Madam,
so I'm busy.

214
00:13:32,800 --> 00:13:34,400
Honestly, this guy...

215
00:13:34,900 --> 00:13:37,233
Just go wait in the car already.

216
00:13:38,733 --> 00:13:41,433
There's a reason people say
the old hand is the best hand.

217
00:13:47,000 --> 00:13:48,700
And what's with that hat now?

218
00:13:49,133 --> 00:13:50,833
It's not like we're out on a golf course.

219
00:13:51,200 --> 00:13:54,300
Mr. Ju, please go wait outside
and stop worrying about me.

220
00:13:55,033 --> 00:13:57,633
She's such an oddball.

221
00:14:01,100 --> 00:14:02,100
All done.

222
00:14:02,800 --> 00:14:04,700
Bit Na,
are you all ready for kindergarten?

223
00:14:04,700 --> 00:14:05,700
Yes.

224
00:14:06,233 --> 00:14:07,233
What about Team Manager Ko?

225
00:14:07,700 --> 00:14:09,000
I think he left for work early.

226
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:10,900
When I woke up, he was already gone.

227
00:14:12,900 --> 00:14:13,900
Really?

228
00:14:14,900 --> 00:14:16,100
Let's all go inside and eat breakfast.

229
00:14:16,200 --> 00:14:18,100
- Okay, let's go.
- Let's go.

230
00:14:22,933 --> 00:14:25,500
Did you two actually have
a lovers' quarrel or something?

231
00:14:26,233 --> 00:14:28,100
Come on in before the soup gets cold.

232
00:14:28,100 --> 00:14:29,100
Yes, Mom.

233
00:14:32,800 --> 00:14:34,100
(Kangsu Construction)

234
00:14:42,333 --> 00:14:44,733
You're making this awkward
for the person who got rejected.

235
00:14:45,600 --> 00:14:47,400
Why did you come to work
without even eating?

236
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:49,800
Besides, it's usually the person
who got dumped...

237
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:52,700
who stops eating,
not the one who did the rejecting.

238
00:14:54,633 --> 00:14:56,733
I think you've got the wrong idea.

239
00:14:58,000 --> 00:14:59,500
I came in early because...

240
00:14:59,500 --> 00:15:01,200
I had an idea
about the retirement community at dawn.

241
00:15:01,900 --> 00:15:03,733
I wasn't running away to avoid you.

242
00:15:05,200 --> 00:15:07,500
So that's what it was.

243
00:15:08,400 --> 00:15:10,833
Did you pack this lunch?

244
00:15:11,533 --> 00:15:12,533
Yes, kind of.

245
00:15:12,900 --> 00:15:15,033
I just put the side dishes Mom made
into containers.

246
00:15:15,633 --> 00:15:18,733
Anyway, one of our family's rules...

247
00:15:18,900 --> 00:15:21,200
is that no family member
should ever skip a meal.

248
00:15:21,833 --> 00:15:22,900
Family member?

249
00:15:24,233 --> 00:15:27,000
Does that include me too?

250
00:15:27,633 --> 00:15:31,200
Of course. We live under the same roof
and eat together.

251
00:15:31,600 --> 00:15:33,000
What else would you call that
if not family?

252
00:15:35,300 --> 00:15:36,300
So I'm family too.

253
00:15:37,600 --> 00:15:40,300
By the way, what was the idea
you came up with at dawn?

254
00:15:42,333 --> 00:15:44,233
What if we set up
something like a remote Tapgol Park...

255
00:15:44,600 --> 00:15:47,700
that works both online and offline
in this shared space,

256
00:15:47,700 --> 00:15:49,800
so seniors can play Go or Korean chess...

257
00:15:49,800 --> 00:15:51,833
regardless of where they are?

258
00:15:52,800 --> 00:15:54,200
A remote Tapgol Park?

259
00:15:54,500 --> 00:15:59,000
Yes. I recently read an article saying
the Go and chess boards at Tapgol Park...

260
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:02,000
were removed for the first time
in 30 years, and it stayed on my mind.

261
00:16:02,500 --> 00:16:05,500
So I thought it might be nice
to create a similar space for our project.

262
00:16:06,500 --> 00:16:10,233
We could install touchscreen LED
Go and chess boards here...

263
00:16:10,600 --> 00:16:12,233
and allow people to connect remotely...

264
00:16:12,233 --> 00:16:13,733
through laptops or smartphones.

265
00:16:14,500 --> 00:16:15,500
That's exactly it.

266
00:16:16,100 --> 00:16:18,900
Not just for our residents,
but something everyone can share together.

267
00:16:21,433 --> 00:16:23,800
Good morning,
Team Manager, Ms. Cho Eun Ae.

268
00:16:24,633 --> 00:16:26,600
Hello, Manager Seo.

269
00:16:27,233 --> 00:16:28,233
Hello.

270
00:16:29,500 --> 00:16:31,400
What's that? A lunchbox?

271
00:16:31,800 --> 00:16:35,300
Team Manager came to work
without breakfast,

272
00:16:35,933 --> 00:16:39,433
and my mom receives rent
and meal expenses from him, so...

273
00:16:39,433 --> 00:16:41,400
Do you really need to explain it
in that much detail?

274
00:16:42,333 --> 00:16:43,333
It's my lunch.

275
00:16:44,833 --> 00:16:47,900
Really? I'm thinking about getting takeout
for lunch today too.

276
00:16:48,500 --> 00:16:49,900
Shall we eat together later?

277
00:16:50,400 --> 00:16:52,800
Sorry? Sure. Yes.

278
00:17:06,500 --> 00:17:09,700
Why are all these approval documents
such a mess?

279
00:17:10,600 --> 00:17:13,300
Put them back in alphabetical order.

280
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:15,333
Alphabetical order?

281
00:17:17,200 --> 00:17:18,900
Everything has its proper order.

282
00:17:19,600 --> 00:17:22,433
These documents need to go
to the Chairman's office this morning,

283
00:17:22,700 --> 00:17:25,300
and these are
for tomorrow's executive meeting...

284
00:17:25,300 --> 00:17:27,233
regarding labor union wage negotiations.

285
00:17:27,700 --> 00:17:28,900
And you want it in alphabetical order?

286
00:17:30,100 --> 00:17:32,333
Then, which one is the most urgent?

287
00:17:33,500 --> 00:17:35,600
Just approve them
in the order they're stacked.

288
00:17:36,333 --> 00:17:37,333
Really?

289
00:17:39,533 --> 00:17:43,000
Mr. Cho,
are you giving me instructions now?

290
00:17:43,800 --> 00:17:45,100
No, that's not an instruction.
I was just...

291
00:17:45,100 --> 00:17:46,633
Enough!

292
00:17:47,333 --> 00:17:49,100
What kind of assistant keeps nitpicking...

293
00:17:49,100 --> 00:17:50,900
the company CEO over every little thing?

294
00:17:50,900 --> 00:17:53,200
What is this? Is this insubordination?

295
00:17:57,133 --> 00:17:59,433
Yes, say you'll quit right away.

296
00:17:59,800 --> 00:18:01,633
Say you've had enough of this
and walk out.

297
00:18:01,900 --> 00:18:03,200
Come on!

298
00:18:03,200 --> 00:18:06,200
Please!

299
00:18:12,533 --> 00:18:15,100
Okay, I'll correct it.

300
00:18:15,633 --> 00:18:18,400
No, don't correct it.

301
00:18:19,733 --> 00:18:22,800
It seems like you're having a bad day,
so let's just set that aside for now...

302
00:18:23,600 --> 00:18:25,700
and approve the documents
for the Chairman's office first.

303
00:18:26,000 --> 00:18:27,500
I'll wait outside.

304
00:18:28,733 --> 00:18:31,400
No, wait. Mr. Cho...

305
00:18:33,100 --> 00:18:35,733
This is nuts. Why isn't it working?

306
00:18:36,300 --> 00:18:38,600
He's supposed to get fed up
and quit on the spot.

307
00:18:38,600 --> 00:18:40,500
Why isn't it working?

308
00:18:50,233 --> 00:18:52,900
What's wrong now? Did something happen?

309
00:18:54,333 --> 00:18:56,200
It's not me.

310
00:18:57,100 --> 00:18:58,900
I think CEO Ko is the one with a problem.

311
00:18:59,900 --> 00:19:00,900
What do you mean?

312
00:19:01,800 --> 00:19:05,700
I think he wants me to resign on my own.

313
00:19:07,400 --> 00:19:08,633
Judging from yesterday and today.

314
00:19:10,700 --> 00:19:12,000
You really think so?

315
00:19:12,633 --> 00:19:15,733
Do you know how hard he worked
to make you his assistant?

316
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:20,133
It's probably temporary.

317
00:19:21,433 --> 00:19:22,433
He'll be back to normal soon...

318
00:19:26,433 --> 00:19:27,433
Hello?

319
00:19:28,800 --> 00:19:32,400
What? You've found that person?

320
00:19:35,400 --> 00:19:39,233
Yes. I'll verify it myself
before reporting to the Chairman.

321
00:19:39,800 --> 00:19:41,700
Please arrange a meeting.

322
00:19:44,500 --> 00:19:47,300
Who exactly is the Chairman looking for?

323
00:19:48,400 --> 00:19:49,400
Actually...

324
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:53,900
No. It's not time to talk about it yet.

325
00:19:58,733 --> 00:20:00,100
What was it you wanted to tell me?

326
00:20:01,400 --> 00:20:03,800
Madam,

327
00:20:04,733 --> 00:20:07,700
what do you think of Seung Ri?

328
00:20:08,400 --> 00:20:09,900
What do I think of her?

329
00:20:10,800 --> 00:20:14,400
Seung Ri is pretty, smart, and kind.

330
00:20:14,633 --> 00:20:16,400
There's nothing lacking in her.

331
00:20:16,800 --> 00:20:17,800
Why do you ask?

332
00:20:18,100 --> 00:20:20,900
As you know,

333
00:20:21,400 --> 00:20:23,400
Seung Ri only has eyes for Gyeol.

334
00:20:24,200 --> 00:20:28,000
Lately, she's been suffering so much
because of him,

335
00:20:28,600 --> 00:20:30,200
and it breaks my heart.

336
00:20:30,300 --> 00:20:32,233
My goodness.

337
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:35,500
People's hearts
don't always go the way we want.

338
00:20:36,033 --> 00:20:38,233
That's why I wanted to ask...

339
00:20:39,133 --> 00:20:41,900
Gyeol listens to you and his grandfather,

340
00:20:42,600 --> 00:20:46,500
so if the Chairman and you
could persuade him...

341
00:20:47,233 --> 00:20:48,233
Us?

342
00:20:48,400 --> 00:20:51,833
Yes. While the Chairman
is still healthy and strong,

343
00:20:52,300 --> 00:20:54,533
wouldn't it make him so happy
to see Gyeol get married,

344
00:20:55,033 --> 00:20:57,233
and to welcome a granddaughter-in-law?

345
00:20:57,400 --> 00:21:00,233
Of course,
we'd love to have a granddaughter-in-law.

346
00:21:01,233 --> 00:21:04,533
But if that's not what Gyeol wants,
what could we possibly do?

347
00:21:05,633 --> 00:21:07,833
That's true.

348
00:21:08,800 --> 00:21:10,400
If Gyeol's heart isn't in it at all...

349
00:21:12,100 --> 00:21:14,333
Please don't worry too much.

350
00:21:14,933 --> 00:21:18,000
I was desperate, so I thought...

351
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:19,400
I'd at least bring it up.

352
00:21:21,500 --> 00:21:22,500
You startled me.

353
00:21:23,300 --> 00:21:24,700
What's with that hat?

354
00:21:25,100 --> 00:21:27,700
What do you think? It's a hat.

355
00:21:28,600 --> 00:21:30,033
I just wanted some water, Mother.

356
00:21:30,700 --> 00:21:33,800
Right, did everything go well
at the real estate office that day?

357
00:21:33,800 --> 00:21:35,433
What? Real estate office?

358
00:21:36,300 --> 00:21:38,000
Well, I...

359
00:21:38,600 --> 00:21:39,600
Jeong Ran.

360
00:21:40,100 --> 00:21:43,200
I made several side dishes today.

361
00:21:43,900 --> 00:21:46,733
Since you're here, stay for lunch.
I'll make you bibimbap.

362
00:21:47,300 --> 00:21:50,433
No, I should be the one cooking for you.

363
00:21:50,533 --> 00:21:51,733
Come on.

364
00:21:52,200 --> 00:21:54,800
Call Mr. Cho's wife too.

365
00:21:55,300 --> 00:21:57,100
I promised I'd cook her a meal sometime.

366
00:21:57,300 --> 00:21:58,400
No, Mother!

367
00:21:59,100 --> 00:22:00,233
Why not?

368
00:22:01,100 --> 00:22:04,100
Aren't the three of you
taking the same dancing classes?

369
00:22:05,300 --> 00:22:08,200
What's wrong with sharing a casual meal?

370
00:22:08,200 --> 00:22:09,733
How could the Chairman's wife...

371
00:22:09,900 --> 00:22:13,300
cook for an ordinary assistant's wife?

372
00:22:13,400 --> 00:22:14,500
Absolutely not. Not a chance.

373
00:22:15,300 --> 00:22:19,200
I also wanted to return the favor
for the soup she brought me.

374
00:22:19,400 --> 00:22:20,700
And I need to return the container.

375
00:22:20,700 --> 00:22:22,000
The container?

376
00:22:22,633 --> 00:22:25,200
I'll return it myself. Okay?

377
00:22:30,133 --> 00:22:31,133
You two keep talking.

378
00:22:31,500 --> 00:22:32,500
Yes, Madam.

379
00:22:37,500 --> 00:22:41,400
Did something happen again
when you went to see Kang Yeon Ja?

380
00:22:43,600 --> 00:22:46,700
Kang Yeon Ja is going to drive me crazy.

381
00:22:47,233 --> 00:22:50,200
From now on, don't even mention
the letter "K" in front of me. Got it?

382
00:22:52,133 --> 00:22:55,333
Is someone talking about me?
My ears keep itching.

383
00:22:59,100 --> 00:23:01,400
Where on earth is her mom?

384
00:23:02,233 --> 00:23:03,733
Doesn't she miss her own child?

385
00:23:07,433 --> 00:23:09,433
It's almost time
for kindergarten pickup already.

386
00:23:13,533 --> 00:23:16,300
What?
You want me to invite Grandpa and Grandma?

387
00:23:16,833 --> 00:23:20,100
Yes. Grandma has already been there,

388
00:23:20,500 --> 00:23:23,500
but don't you think Grandpa is curious
about the place you live?

389
00:23:24,300 --> 00:23:27,500
You have no idea
how much your grandfather adores you,

390
00:23:27,900 --> 00:23:28,900
do you?

391
00:23:29,300 --> 00:23:30,300
Of course I do.

392
00:23:30,500 --> 00:23:32,933
But I should ask the landlord first.

393
00:23:33,933 --> 00:23:36,200
Ask quickly,
and invite them no matter what.

394
00:23:36,800 --> 00:23:37,900
The sooner, the better.

395
00:23:39,033 --> 00:23:40,033
What?

396
00:23:41,000 --> 00:23:42,733
No, I mean...

397
00:23:42,733 --> 00:23:45,700
Before Grandpa's health gets any worse,
you should be a good grandson.

398
00:23:46,900 --> 00:23:48,833
But where exactly is your place?

399
00:23:48,833 --> 00:23:50,700
Somewhere near the company?

400
00:23:50,900 --> 00:23:52,400
No.
It's actually a bit far from the office.

401
00:23:53,300 --> 00:23:57,000
Really? Then I'll make some time soon...

402
00:23:57,233 --> 00:23:59,000
and come visit your place too.

403
00:23:59,200 --> 00:24:00,900
That's not necessary.

404
00:24:01,400 --> 00:24:02,800
I'll be going now.

405
00:24:03,000 --> 00:24:04,333
Okay.

406
00:24:10,100 --> 00:24:11,333
Absolutely.

407
00:24:11,800 --> 00:24:14,200
Checking the content of the will
in that safe...

408
00:24:14,200 --> 00:24:16,400
is the most important thing. Exactly.

409
00:24:19,233 --> 00:24:21,933
We believe in high risk, high return.

410
00:24:22,200 --> 00:24:26,033
Simply put, aggressive early investment
followed by massive profits.

411
00:24:26,033 --> 00:24:28,200
High risk, high return
also means high danger.

412
00:24:28,533 --> 00:24:30,600
You need a contingency plan for failure...

413
00:24:30,600 --> 00:24:32,400
if you want to convince the judges.

414
00:24:33,100 --> 00:24:35,900
Mr. Han Ji Hun,
how is the Joy upgrade coming along?

415
00:24:36,000 --> 00:24:40,200
From what I can see, it doesn't seem
very different from the existing Joy.

416
00:24:40,433 --> 00:24:41,600
It feels like a lack of creativity.

417
00:24:42,300 --> 00:24:44,200
I'm curious.

418
00:24:44,733 --> 00:24:47,600
What makes you think
it's lacking creativity?

419
00:24:47,600 --> 00:24:49,400
Compared to the original Joy
that Ms. Cho Eun Ae outlined,

420
00:24:49,400 --> 00:24:50,800
there's not much that's changed.

421
00:24:51,500 --> 00:24:53,900
It's basically
just a fully personalized assistant...

422
00:24:54,433 --> 00:24:56,700
with a few technical improvements.

423
00:24:56,700 --> 00:24:59,333
What I'm saying is,
there's nothing uniquely new about it.

424
00:25:02,233 --> 00:25:05,100
I think it might be a good idea...

425
00:25:05,433 --> 00:25:08,100
to conduct a survey among seniors.

426
00:25:08,600 --> 00:25:09,633
That's a good idea.

427
00:25:10,000 --> 00:25:11,833
Ms. Ha Yu Ju,
please take charge of the survey.

428
00:25:13,333 --> 00:25:15,933
The real work begins now. Understood?

429
00:25:17,500 --> 00:25:20,400
Should we take a break?
We've been going for two hours straight.

430
00:25:21,800 --> 00:25:23,600
Sounds good.
I'll head back to the office for a bit.

431
00:25:24,900 --> 00:25:27,000
Would you like me
to grab drinks from the café, Chief?

432
00:25:27,200 --> 00:25:29,133
Sure. Get a generous variety.

433
00:25:29,133 --> 00:25:30,833
- Yes.
- I'll go with her.

434
00:25:30,833 --> 00:25:31,833
Sure. Go ahead.

435
00:25:36,300 --> 00:25:37,333
What's with Seo Seung Ri?

436
00:25:38,300 --> 00:25:41,533
She seems full of energy.
Something feels different.

437
00:25:43,400 --> 00:25:44,400
Right.

438
00:25:45,333 --> 00:25:47,900
Let's see the business plan materials.

439
00:25:57,500 --> 00:25:58,500
What's this?

440
00:25:58,500 --> 00:25:59,700
(Application for Admission
to the MBA Program)

441
00:26:04,200 --> 00:26:06,700
Bit Na!

442
00:26:09,600 --> 00:26:13,533
Where did she go?
She said she was taking a nap.

443
00:26:16,000 --> 00:26:18,933
Is Bit Na here by any chance?

444
00:26:19,133 --> 00:26:20,900
What? She's not at home?

445
00:26:21,500 --> 00:26:23,100
She never came here today.

446
00:26:23,200 --> 00:26:26,200
She was sleepy and went into her room
after getting back from kindergarten.

447
00:26:27,000 --> 00:26:29,500
I stepped out briefly
to show a house to a client and...

448
00:26:30,800 --> 00:26:31,800
Wait.

449
00:26:32,300 --> 00:26:33,300
Hold on.

450
00:26:34,900 --> 00:26:36,300
Eun Hyeong.

451
00:26:37,033 --> 00:26:39,033
Have you heard from Bit Na?

452
00:26:39,033 --> 00:26:40,400
I can't find her.

453
00:26:42,433 --> 00:26:45,433
Okay. I'll keep looking and call you back.

454
00:26:46,833 --> 00:26:49,000
I'll check the kindergarten
and the playground.

455
00:26:49,000 --> 00:26:50,000
Okay.

456
00:26:50,833 --> 00:26:53,633
Where could she possibly have gone?

457
00:26:54,100 --> 00:26:56,533
Maybe she wanted to see her mom...

458
00:26:58,800 --> 00:26:59,800
What?

459
00:27:05,233 --> 00:27:08,000
Where did she go?

460
00:27:22,900 --> 00:27:23,900
Bit Na!

461
00:27:31,400 --> 00:27:32,733
Grandma.

462
00:27:33,700 --> 00:27:36,733
Why are you here?
How did you get here all by yourself?

463
00:27:37,200 --> 00:27:38,900
The door won't open.

464
00:27:39,500 --> 00:27:41,633
I know the password.

465
00:27:42,033 --> 00:27:43,800
Why won't it open? Why?

466
00:27:44,933 --> 00:27:47,533
I want to go home.

467
00:27:49,233 --> 00:27:51,400
I want to see Mom.

468
00:27:51,800 --> 00:27:54,000
- Mom.
- Bit Na, it's okay.

469
00:27:54,733 --> 00:27:57,200
- Don't cry, Bit Na.
- Mom.

470
00:27:57,400 --> 00:28:00,133
Don't cry. She'll come back soon.
She'll definitely come back.

471
00:28:00,133 --> 00:28:01,200
Don't cry.

472
00:28:04,300 --> 00:28:07,033
- Don't cry.
- I miss Mom.

473
00:28:07,233 --> 00:28:10,200
Mom.

474
00:28:10,400 --> 00:28:13,633
- I miss Mom.
- Mom will come back soon.

475
00:28:16,000 --> 00:28:17,500
There. Don't cry.

476
00:28:26,700 --> 00:28:28,000
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
